sql:
SELECT 
  (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM likes) AS total_likes, 
  (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM comments) AS total_comments;

external_knowledge:
A user's engagement score is a measure of their overall activity on the platform. The scores are calculated based on the following formula:
- Each image post is worth 10 points;
- Each like is worth 5 points;
- Each comment is worth 3 points;
- Each feed is worth 2 points;
- Each trend is worth 7 points;
- Each report is worth -5 points (penalty);
- Each heart like is worth 8 points;
- Each thumbs up like is worth 6 points;
- Each smile like is worth 4 points.
The platform considers a user "active" if they have a high engagement score.
